WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.580 --> 00:00:04.060
- What I wanna talk about
today is recommended

00:00:05.360 --> 00:00:07.603
nutrition specifically,

00:00:08.510 --> 00:00:11.070
micro nutrients or vitamins,

00:00:11.070 --> 00:00:13.740
antioxidants and cellfirm
are in that same category.

00:00:13.740 --> 00:00:16.500
So, we've been told
ever since we were kids,

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:17.840
your mother told you
you need your vitamins,

00:00:17.840 --> 00:00:18.840
you need to eat your vegetables

00:00:18.840 --> 00:00:20.290
cause you need your vitamins.

00:00:20.290 --> 00:00:22.573
So the question is,

00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:25.963
are the recommendations correct?

00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:28.883
And then the second question is,

00:00:30.830 --> 00:00:32.910
judged by what?

00:00:32.910 --> 00:00:37.210
Like long life, disease
avoidance, performance.

00:00:37.210 --> 00:00:38.390
Clearly not performance,

00:00:38.390 --> 00:00:41.360
we will be measuring
performance for the last,

00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:43.750
let's say, 100 years really.

00:00:43.750 --> 00:00:46.750
And a lot of these recommendations
are from way before that.

00:00:49.300 --> 00:00:51.780
So lemme start off

00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:55.430
with a study that came out in 2010.

00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:58.298
Now this is in the journal of

00:00:58.298 --> 00:01:01.890
The International Society
of Sports Nutrition.

00:01:01.890 --> 00:01:05.690
So prevalence of micro nutrient deficiency

00:01:05.690 --> 00:01:08.580
and popular diet plans.

00:01:08.580 --> 00:01:10.880
So they compared

00:01:12.070 --> 00:01:14.890
the availability of micronutrients

00:01:14.890 --> 00:01:17.560
in varying different types of plants.

00:01:17.560 --> 00:01:22.560
So they compared the DASH
diet, the South Beach diet,

00:01:22.610 --> 00:01:25.710
the Atkins diet, which is
basically just the ketogenic diet

00:01:27.580 --> 00:01:30.793
and I believe one other.

00:01:32.910 --> 00:01:35.020
No, it was it was those three.

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:38.403
So DASH and South Beach are heading in,

00:01:39.580 --> 00:01:43.853
I think DASH is pretty much
all vegetables and some meats,

00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:48.380
in South Beach is somewhere in between

00:01:48.380 --> 00:01:52.550
and Atkins is primarily meats

00:01:52.550 --> 00:01:53.770
and animal products

00:01:53.770 --> 00:01:56.690
and then animal proteins I should say.

00:01:56.690 --> 00:01:59.660
And then it's.

00:01:59.660 --> 00:02:02.460
Move the microphone a little closer to me.

00:02:02.460 --> 00:02:03.293
Yeah.

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:07.110
And then vegetables.

00:02:07.110 --> 00:02:12.110
So what was looked at was
to the get the recommended

00:02:12.330 --> 00:02:16.120
daily values, what was required?

00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:18.853
What was the nutrient
value that was required?

00:02:20.670 --> 00:02:22.980
How many calories were required

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:26.440
for somebody to get
this level of nutrients

00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:28.480
from the recommended daily

00:02:30.140 --> 00:02:35.140
intakes administered by the
FDA or published by the FDA.

00:02:35.430 --> 00:02:40.430
So the answer was 27,000 calories

00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:44.840
of whole foods would need
to be ingested on average

00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:49.840
to get to the minimum dosages
of the 27 micronutrients.

00:02:52.743 --> 00:02:54.847
27,000 calories per day.

00:02:55.790 --> 00:02:59.020
So my question when reading this

00:02:59.020 --> 00:03:01.010
now of course, the conclusion in study is,

00:03:01.010 --> 00:03:03.713
so people definitely need
to take a multivitamin.

00:03:05.160 --> 00:03:08.690
Or the recommended daily intake

00:03:09.530 --> 00:03:11.373
by the FDA is,

00:03:12.560 --> 00:03:14.150
something wrong with it.

00:03:14.150 --> 00:03:14.983
Doesn't make any sense

00:03:14.983 --> 00:03:16.360
because last I checked

00:03:18.380 --> 00:03:21.160
homo sapiens we're
thriving on this planet,

00:03:21.160 --> 00:03:23.274
and they didn't,

00:03:23.274 --> 00:03:26.290
they certainly didn't eat
27,000 calories per day.

00:03:26.290 --> 00:03:28.220
And also, you have to consider

00:03:28.220 --> 00:03:32.020
that just about anybody
from just about any place.

00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:34.720
Maybe ate one or two
different types of things.

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:36.973
If you were a Native
American, you ate bison,

00:03:37.990 --> 00:03:39.620
and maybe some kind of berries

00:03:39.620 --> 00:03:41.640
or plants when they were blooming.

00:03:41.640 --> 00:03:43.470
Like for a couple weeks,

00:03:43.470 --> 00:03:44.960
that's about it.

00:03:44.960 --> 00:03:48.173
And if you're a Viking
you're eating whale blubber.

00:03:49.750 --> 00:03:52.650
If you were some Nordic countries,

00:03:52.650 --> 00:03:53.970
I shouldn't call the Vikings.

00:03:53.970 --> 00:03:55.860
I'm not sure that's offensive or not.

00:03:55.860 --> 00:03:57.570
Actually they should find that pretty cool

00:03:57.570 --> 00:03:58.970
because Vikings are awesome.

00:04:02.350 --> 00:04:05.590
Let's see if you were from, you know,

00:04:05.590 --> 00:04:09.350
Mediterranean you ate fish
because that's what was there.

00:04:09.350 --> 00:04:13.660
So the idea these micronutrients
are just so required for

00:04:14.650 --> 00:04:18.980
for disease avoidance is kind
of strange, kind of silly.

00:04:18.980 --> 00:04:20.527
And it seems an awful lot like

00:04:20.527 --> 00:04:23.740
the people who wrote those
recommendations were like

00:04:23.740 --> 00:04:27.740
in a vitamin sales business,
just seems that way.

00:04:27.740 --> 00:04:29.670
I mean, hey, that's conspiracy theory

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:32.480
and maybe these things
were developed out of

00:04:33.810 --> 00:04:37.170
some sort of responsibility
though you know,

00:04:37.170 --> 00:04:40.420
we don't really know these
came a long time ago.

00:04:40.420 --> 00:04:43.760
But then after this,
there was a 2011 study

00:04:43.760 --> 00:04:46.000
from the University of Minnesota,

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:48.100
which showed that people
that took multivitamins

00:04:48.100 --> 00:04:51.670
died younger than people who
do not take multivitamins.

00:04:51.670 --> 00:04:56.430
The same year Cleveland
Clinic came up with vitamin E

00:04:57.620 --> 00:05:01.793
being attributed to higher
prevalence of prostate cancer.

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:09.090
And these recommendations may

00:05:10.170 --> 00:05:15.110
all go back to actually or at
least on the higher levels,

00:05:15.110 --> 00:05:17.860
the talk track about vitamins.

00:05:17.860 --> 00:05:21.160
It became much more popular in the 1940s,

00:05:21.160 --> 00:05:24.490
when Linus Pauling started saying you have

00:05:24.490 --> 00:05:26.490
10 times the recommended daily allowance

00:05:28.904 --> 00:05:30.850
of vitamin C,

00:05:30.850 --> 00:05:32.200
you're never gonna get a cold

00:05:32.200 --> 00:05:34.310
or you have a cold go away.

00:05:34.310 --> 00:05:38.450
And that was tested a number
of times after he said it

00:05:38.450 --> 00:05:42.000
and that was found to be untrue.

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:45.060
Though, it was exciting and

00:05:45.060 --> 00:05:49.600
possibly the press picks up
on exciting things more often

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:51.603
than they pick up on,

00:05:53.950 --> 00:05:54.783
you know.

00:05:55.940 --> 00:05:58.070
Something that's not so
exciting or bad news.

00:05:58.070 --> 00:06:00.440
So it was hopeful and

00:06:01.370 --> 00:06:05.323
then after that was pretty well disproven.

00:06:09.450 --> 00:06:13.550
Professor Pauling started
saying that vitamin C was also

00:06:13.550 --> 00:06:18.550
the cure for cancer, which was
also very quickly disproven.

00:06:19.130 --> 00:06:24.130
And the despite winning, I
think was two Nobel prizes,

00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:28.360
he wasn't very popular after that

00:06:28.360 --> 00:06:30.690
because he just kinda
made these things up.

00:06:30.690 --> 00:06:33.940
And the other interesting
argument about antioxidants.

00:06:33.940 --> 00:06:37.220
So this is really why we
talk about antioxidants.

00:06:37.220 --> 00:06:40.940
Antioxidants are really
where electrons are borrowed

00:06:42.130 --> 00:06:45.510
to stop something that is oxidizing.

00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:47.950
So again, interesting theory.

00:06:47.950 --> 00:06:51.290
Now that also is predicated on the idea

00:06:52.290 --> 00:06:55.960
that you have inflammation,

00:06:55.960 --> 00:06:58.700
you're oxidizing on the
inside of your body.

00:06:58.700 --> 00:07:00.890
When we have an anti-inflammatory diet,

00:07:00.890 --> 00:07:04.100
like a ketogenic diet or a carnivore diet,

00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:06.410
well then don't you have inflammation.

00:07:06.410 --> 00:07:08.960
So what would you need in antioxidants for

00:07:08.960 --> 00:07:10.173
if you're not oxidizing?

00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:13.190
You wouldn't.

00:07:13.190 --> 00:07:16.670
So also, there's sort of a logic problem

00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:19.440
that you need to have this one thing

00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:21.830
to keep from all these

00:07:23.130 --> 00:07:24.470
things that come from vegetables,

00:07:24.470 --> 00:07:26.590
which are poisonous from hurting you.

00:07:26.590 --> 00:07:28.940
So you have to have
derivatives of other vegetables

00:07:28.940 --> 00:07:30.100
and fruits,

00:07:30.100 --> 00:07:33.770
the antioxidants to protect
you from these things.

00:07:33.770 --> 00:07:35.240
Which just seems

00:07:38.640 --> 00:07:40.633
illogical to me.

00:07:42.130 --> 00:07:44.160
And it's a bit of an oversimplification

00:07:44.160 --> 00:07:45.800
but ultimately,

00:07:45.800 --> 00:07:49.320
even a Harvard School of Public Health

00:07:49.320 --> 00:07:51.880
has said some pretty

00:07:54.050 --> 00:07:56.170
strong things about antioxidants

00:07:56.170 --> 00:07:57.570
and vitamins in general.

00:07:57.570 --> 00:08:00.070
And just pointing out

00:08:00.070 --> 00:08:02.420
it's not saying "Don't go and
take any of these things,"

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:05.130
just saying there's a lot of hype there

00:08:05.130 --> 00:08:06.650
and may not be the

00:08:09.670 --> 00:08:13.313
validity there that you are,

00:08:14.860 --> 00:08:18.260
you are looking for that
may be protecting you.

00:08:18.260 --> 00:08:22.230
So hence a Falsehood of Fitness episode

00:08:22.230 --> 00:08:25.553
on vitamins and micronutrients.

